LucyX-Search-WildcardQuery

LucyX::Search::WildcardQuery is an extension to Lucy::Search::Query
for wildcard terms, like 'foo*' and 'ba?r'.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc LucyX::Search::WildcardQuery

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=LucyX-Search-WildcardQuery

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/LucyX-Search-WildcardQuery

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/LucyX-Search-WildcardQuery

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/LucyX-Search-WildcardQuery/


